This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with cross-view video understanding, which is a key area in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a joint parsing framework that integrates view-centric proposals into scene-centric parse graphs, which is a common approach in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves the use of commonsense knowledge, which is a key area in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper proposes a framework that generates semantic scene-centric parse graphs, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning and graph-based methods. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques to represent consistency constraints available in commonsense knowledge, which is a key area in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
